#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading the Stage Tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:122
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Go to the Gentoo mountpoint at which you mounted your filesystems\n"
"(most likely <path>/mnt/gentoo</path>):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "Going to the Gentoo mountpoint"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:131
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Depending on your installation medium, you have a couple of tools available to\n"
"download a stage. If you have <c>links2</c> available, then you can immediately\n"
"surf to <uri link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">the Gentoo mirrorlist</uri> and \n"
"choose a mirror close to you.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you don't have <c>links2</c> available you should have <c>lynx</c> at your \n"
"disposal. If you need to go through a proxy, export the <c>http_proxy</c> and\n"
"<c>ftp_proxy</c> variables:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:143
#, no-wrap
msgid "Setting proxy information for lynx"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:144
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>export http_proxy=\"http://proxy.server.com:port\"</i>\n"
"# <i>export ftp_proxy=\"http://proxy.server.com:port\"</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "We will now assume that you have <c>links2</c> at your disposal.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Pick the <path>releases/</path> directory, followed by your architecture (for \n"
"instance <path>x86/</path>) and the Gentoo version (<path>2004.3/</path>) \n"
"to finish up with the <path>stages/</path> directory. There you should see all \n"
"available stage files for your architecture (they might be stored within\n"
"subdirectories named to the individual sub architectures). Select one and \n"
"press <c>D</c> to download. When you're finished, press <c>Q</c> to quit the \n"
"browser.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:162
#, no-wrap
msgid "Surfing to the mirror listing with links2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>links2 http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(If you need proxy support with links2:)</comment>\n"
"# <i>links2 -http-proxy proxy.server.com:8080 http://www.gentoo.org/main/en/mirrors.xml</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you want to check the integrity of the downloaded stage tarball, use\n"
"<c>md5sum</c> and compare the output with the MD5 checksum provided on the\n"
"mirror. For instance, to check the validity of the x86 stage tarball:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "Example checking integrity of a stage tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:176
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>md5sum -c stage1-x86-2004.3.tar.bz2.md5</i>\n"
"stage1-x86-2004.3.tar.bz2: OK\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unpacking the Stage Tarball"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:187
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now unpack your downloaded stage onto your system. We use GNU's <c>tar</c> to\n"
"proceed as it is the easiest method:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unpacking the stage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:192
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>tar -xvjpf stage?-*.tar.bz2</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:196
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Make sure that you use the same options (<c>-xvjpf</c>). The <c>x</c> stands for\n"
"<e>Extract</e>, the <c>v</c> for <e>Verbose</e> (okay, yes, this is optional),\n"
"the <c>j</c> for <e>Decompress with bzip2</e>, the <c>p</c> for <e>Preserve\n"
"permissions</e> and the <c>f</c> to denote that we want to extract a file, not\n"
"standard input.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:212
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing Portage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unpacking a Portage Snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:218
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You now have to install a Portage snapshot, a collection of files that inform\n"
"Portage what software titles you can install, which profiles are available, etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unpack the Snapshot from the LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To install the snapshot, take a look inside <path>/mnt/cdrom/snapshots/</path> \n"
"to see what snapshot is available:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "Checking the /mnt/cdrom/snapshots content"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:234
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>ls /mnt/cdrom/snapshots</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:238
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now extract the snapshot using the following construct. Again, make sure you\n"
"use the correct options with <c>tar</c>. Also, the <c>-C</c> is with a capital\n"
"<c>C</c>, not <c>c</c>. In the next example we use\n"
"<path>portage-20041022.tar.bz2</path> as the snapshot filename. Be sure to\n"
"substitute with the name of the snapshot that is on your LiveCD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:245
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extracting a Portage snapshot"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:246
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>tar -xvjf /mnt/cdrom/snapshots/portage-20041022.tar.bz2 -C /mnt/gentoo/usr</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copy Source Code Archives"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.3/hb-install-stage.xml:256
#, no-wrap
